==English==

===Noun===
'''clarinet'''
{{Wikipedia}}
#{{music}} A [[woodwind]] musical instrument that has a distinctive liquid tone whose characteristics vary among its three registers: chalumeau (low), clarion (medium), and altissimo (high).
====Etymology====
Learned borrowing from Italian ''clarinetto'', diminutive of ''clarino'' meaning "[[trumpet]]" (as the first clarinets had a strident tone similar to that of a trumpet)

